Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.49,0:00:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.13,0:00:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This letter from my friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.87,0:00:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,My best friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.54,0:00:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were 15, we tried to cross\Nthe Czech border together.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.01,0:00:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She was caught\Nand taken to Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.78,0:00:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,She says she's doing fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.18,0:00:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,She knows me better than\Nmy parents or my siblings.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.42,0:00:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a true friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.96,0:00:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows how much trouble\Nshe went through to get this to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.79,0:00:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,with all the government's\Nharsh inspections.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.73,0:00:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She says, "Please visit me\Nif you have the chance."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.67,0:00:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,"Cedok Bridge,\NThree Frogs"...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.84,0:01:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go back to Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.48,0:01:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.92,0:01:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.23,0:01:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Call me by my real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.83,0:01:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Just for today, I want you to\Ncall me by my real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.47,0:01:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Helenka Novakova.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.88,0:01:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Just for today,\NI'm not Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.67,0:03:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I sold my stocks in Reiser-Berger\NPharmaceuticals at the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.14,0:03:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, when I bought some stocks in\NKnutter Laboratories, I hit the jackpot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.38,0:03:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it was cause\Nfor celebration, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.22,0:03:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You had a drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.62,0:03:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Just a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.59,0:03:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.25,0:03:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just one drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.89,0:03:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.22,0:03:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,For an alcoholic, drinking just a little\Nis the same as drinking a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.66,0:03:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't seem like you've been going to\Nthe alcohol relief group I introduced you to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.20,0:03:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way. .. Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.64,0:03:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, you can keep a secret,\Ncan't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.61,0:03:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, there's a woman\NI want you to meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.38,0:03:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You have another mistress?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.78,0:03:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.08,0:03:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She's also\Na pretty bad alcoholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.02,0:03:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She's waiting outside right now.\NCould you see her for a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.62,0:04:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Not suddenly like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.69,0:04:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Make an appointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.86,0:04:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Just for a little while\Nwill be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.96,0:04:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a house call right now.\NIt's for an important client.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.70,0:04:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to Prague\Nin the Czech Republic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.34,0:04:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a really nice place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.71,0:04:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Prague Castle...\NWonderful Gothic cathedrals...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.61,0:04:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beautiful when\Nthe old town plaza lights up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.62,0:04:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a village\Nout of a fairytale.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.92,0:04:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Cedok Bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.85,0:04:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you go to Cedok Bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.66,0:04:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.72,0:04:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I did as you told me to do\Nand I found it. Even the three frogs!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.64,0:04:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Was the woman there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.00,0:04:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No. No one was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.04,0:04:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I didn't learn\Nanything by going there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.85,0:04:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't find anything\Non Tenma's whereabouts,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.01,0:05:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and I also couldn't find anything\Non Nina and Dieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.49,0:05:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.79,0:05:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lucky rabbit's foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.50,0:05:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you give it to\Nour soon-to-be child.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.67,0:05:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot... No, Helenka... I ...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.38,0:05:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.94,0:06:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.95,0:06:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.41,0:06:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come from Germany\Nin search of a woman
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.88,0:06:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,whose whereabouts\Nare unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.99,0:06:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know a woman by the name of\NMargot Langerâ€“no, Helenka Novakova?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.03,0:06:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Helenka...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.93,0:06:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Mr. Schuwald...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.40,0:06:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard from your son, Karl.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.47,0:06:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't been able\Nto eat properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.84,0:06:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You had a petrifying experience at the\Nfire in the University of Munich library.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.58,0:06:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that the fear\Nstill hasn't left you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.82,0:06:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have Karl...\NA wonderful son.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.90,0:06:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You have nothing more\Nto worry about!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.13,0:06:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure to eat more.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.10,0:07:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.34,0:07:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as that\Nmonster exists.. .I...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.28,0:07:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did that monster know\Nso much about Margot Langer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.09,0:07:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew far more than\Neither her son Karl or I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.26,0:07:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot's best friend, the one who knew her\Nbetter than her parents or her siblings...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.77,0:07:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The woman who Margot\Nexchanged letters with...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.74,0:07:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In the '80s, you searched for Margot,\Nwho had gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.94,0:07:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You went to Prague\Nand met that woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.88,0:07:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I thought that that woman might\Nhave heard something from Margot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.39,0:07:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But she knew nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.02,0:07:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We talked for a while\Nabout Margot at the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.76,0:08:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when they were listening\Nto our conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.07,0:08:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.67,0:08:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They were quietly listening\Nbehind that woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.48,0:08:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The twins...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.71,0:08:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.58,0:08:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.65,0:08:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the person that Mr. Thalbach\Nwanted me to see, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.59,0:08:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't stop drinking either?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.63,0:08:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Make yourself comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.33,0:08:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Just act as if we're\Ngoing to have a little chat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.50,0:08:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.43,0:08:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Mereth?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.57,0:08:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in the middle of counseling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.10,0:08:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,On TV! Right now on TV!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.64,0:08:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Tenma. Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.54,0:08:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me for a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.04,0:08:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I repeat, the Czech police have\Napprehended in Prague{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.68,0:08:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the prime suspect of\Nthe poisoning of three doctors{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.12,0:08:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}of Dusseldorf Germany's\NEisler Memorial Hospital,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.42,0:08:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the murders of the journalist Maurer\Nand the Fortner couple in Heidelberg{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.76,0:09:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and the phantom killing\Nat Heidelberg Castle...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.59,0:09:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the Japanese Doctor Kenzo Tenma was\Napprehended on the afternoon of the fifth.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.77,0:09:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We have not received\Nany further information.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.20,0:09:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We will continue to report the details\Nof how he was taken into custody when{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.47,0:09:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}â€“ the police make their announcement.{\i0}\Nâ€“ Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.91,0:09:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't!\NThis is the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.58,0:09:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait in the consultation room,\NMiss Eva Heinemann!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.78,0:09:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Kenzo...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.38,0:09:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry everyone,\Nfor coming late.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.39,0:09:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hess, you look like you've\Ngotten ten years younger!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.82,0:09:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because I'm always\Nplaying with my grandchild.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.79,0:09:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Huber, how are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.86,0:09:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I've managed to move up\Nto my final academic year!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.77,0:09:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Kieffer, I hear you're\Npretty busy too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.74,0:09:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I was bragging about how\NI'm friends with a scriptwriter
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.27,0:09:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,who's been invited\Nto go to Hollywood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.27,0:09:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I just happened to catch\Nthe eye of one of their producers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.58,0:10:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,My mind has cleared and\Nnew ideas keep coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.88,0:10:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds promising!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.79,0:10:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since that surgery...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.09,0:10:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If my brain operation hadn't\Nbeen successful, I'd be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.86,0:10:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have been able to walk\Nwith my grandchild in the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.60,0:10:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That seat...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.41,0:10:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He always sat there\Ndrinking tea by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.34,0:10:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There were other cafes\Nwhere doctors gathered.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.35,0:10:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But he came to this cafÃ©\Nbehind Eisler Memorial Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.68,0:10:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When we patients\Nwould come in...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.59,0:10:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,...he'd raise his head\Nas he sat there...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.09,0:10:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,...and smile and wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.39,0:10:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a kind doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.19,0:10:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.70,0:10:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a kind doctor. ..\Nwould never do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.14,0:10:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This is why I've\Ngathered everyone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.47,0:11:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No, even the people who couldn't come\Nhere today would feel the same as we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.24,0:11:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They were Dr. Tenma's\Nformer patients, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.38,0:11:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Schumann, bad news!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.62,0:11:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Old man Merkel collapsed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.09,0:11:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! I'll be right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.79,0:11:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm busy right now.\NSorry, but wait for me there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.59,0:11:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.59,0:11:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma never\Ndid those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.50,0:11:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down and\Nlisten to me, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.93,0:11:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to him quickly, Dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.47,0:11:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. But, Petra...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.64,0:11:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No buts! Dr. Tenma was arrested\Nfor a crime he didn't commit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.88,0:11:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If he hadn't been around,\NI wouldn't be alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.08,0:11:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Schumann, don't you care about\Nthe man who saved your wife's life?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.99,0:11:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What'll happen to this village?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.66,0:11:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.69,0:11:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the only doctor in this village.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.83,0:11:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What'll happen to the folks\Nin this town if I'm gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.07,0:11:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't blabber on.\NYou want to go, don't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.97,0:12:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly, go and save Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.14,0:12:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's a patient,\Na doctor mustn't leave him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.58,0:12:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what Dr. Tenma\Nwould do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.25,0:12:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, see us quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.88,0:12:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, I'm getting ready\Nright now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.08,0:12:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How long are you going to\Nmake us wait?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.82,0:12:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't complain!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.35,0:12:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Lately, the doctor has been\Ngoing to medical school.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.09,0:12:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's risky for her to examine\Npatients here illegally!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.23,0:12:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When you're in darkness,\Nyou just sink deeper into it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.87,0:12:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Shine some light.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.27,0:12:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You can do it!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.61,0:12:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You can become\Na good doctor.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.61,0:12:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.76,0:12:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to start examining patients!\NWhoever's first come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.46,0:12:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.89,0:12:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.13,0:13:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But we still don't know where in\NGermany Tenma will be transferred to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.04,0:13:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Retain an attorney\Nfrom each state.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.74,0:13:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the best criminal attorney.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.88,0:13:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.81,0:13:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the only one...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.61,0:13:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the only man who\Ncan erase the monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.79,0:13:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,First off, we need to\Nget more allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.03,0:13:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's call Dr. Tenma's\Nformer patients!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.53,0:13:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We may be weak as individuals,\Nbut if we join together...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.97,0:13:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.44,0:13:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask Eisler Memorial Hospital\Nfor help in forming a relief group.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.54,0:13:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.88,0:13:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Eisler Memorial Hospital won't\Nhelp you with something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.52,0:13:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I was listening to you.\NIt was quite a touching story.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.29,0:14:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But think hard about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.43,0:14:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How will you prove\NTenma's innocence?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.23,0:14:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Becker...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.33,0:14:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He has some motive,\Nbut no alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.90,0:14:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They even say that\Nthere's physical evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.14,0:14:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you gather numbers\Nand make a lot of noise...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.48,0:14:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no matter how brilliant\Na lawyer you hire...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.68,0:14:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what, it's impossible\Nto prove Tenma's innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.56,0:14:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How unfortunate for\Nsuch a brilliant doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.76,0:14:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly unfortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.13,0:14:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ask you once more...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.17,0:14:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your relationship\Nto Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.08,0:14:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Eva Heinemann...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.71,0:15:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who you are,\Nbut I'm going to go save Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.92,0:15:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want you to come with me\Nif you're just going to sightsee.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.09,0:15:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva... Heinemann...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.89,0:15:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Heinemann!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.43,0:15:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Heinemann...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.56,0:15:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that you're the daughter\Nof Director Heinemann,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.70,0:15:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,who was killed at Eisler Hospital\Nin DÃ¼sseldorf?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.97,0:15:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.94,0:15:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the man that\Ndestroyed my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.18,0:15:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm the only one\Nwho can save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.41,0:15:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.02,0:15:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.32,0:15:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Saw what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.79,0:15:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kenzo Tenma is being\Ndetained in Prague.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.90,0:15:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He will be deported to Germany\Nin a day or two.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.13,0:15:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's being moved to DÃ¼sseldorf\Nwhere it is believed these incidents began.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.77,0:15:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After interrogation...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.74,0:15:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.38,0:16:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.28,0:16:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This person is...\NThis doctor is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.18,0:16:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is Dr. Tenma.\NSuk, he saved your life.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.19,0:16:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He applied first aid.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.82,0:16:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's also been framed for\Na crime he didn't commit.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.99,0:16:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's in the same\Nsituation you are.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.90,0:16:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Saved my life.\NSame situation as me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.23,0:16:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You're a detective\Naren't you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.37,0:16:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you're a detective,\Nyou must dissect everything calmly.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.94,0:16:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you don't want to be\Nbetrayed anymore,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.75,0:16:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}doubt the people you don't\Never want to doubt.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.59,0:16:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.19,0:16:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I've got to go to\NPrague station and talk to Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.64,0:17:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been looking for you, Suk.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.20,0:17:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Detective Bradec,\NDetective Stransky...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.87,0:17:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.81,0:17:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to\Nrun away anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.91,0:17:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.98,0:17:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You must have had\Na terrible time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.92,0:17:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been cleared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.12,0:17:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,A letter was sent to the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.49,0:17:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.62,0:17:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.82,0:17:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a confession that gives\Nthe details of all the events
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.16,0:17:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that only the culprit\Nwould know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.26,0:17:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been cleared\Nof all suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.46,0:17:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Who sent this letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.73,0:17:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A man who goes\Nby the name Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.94,0:17:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.24,0:17:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Grimmer has been put on\Nthe wanted list as a prime suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.18,0:17:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.51,0:17:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Relax, Suk.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.98,0:17:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Zeman's murder,\Nthe chief's poisoning,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.18,0:17:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and the shooting of the special\Ninvestigations team have all been solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.19,0:19:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Where have you been,\NLunge?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.19,0:19:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I called you\Nso many times!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.19,0:19:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Chief,\NI was doing some sightseeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.10,0:19:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Honestly!\NDon't act dumb!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.87,0:19:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Act dumb?\NWhat are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.60,0:19:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Cut it out! Don't tell me you\Nhaven't heard the news!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.54,0:19:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Are you talking about\NDr. Tenma's arrest?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.11,0:19:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Congratulations, Lunge!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.05,0:19:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.88,0:19:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You knew that Tenma was\Nhiding in Prague, didn't you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.38,0:19:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Good work, Lunge!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.22,0:19:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Your persistent investigation\Nhas paid off.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.12,0:19:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We've finished talking\Nto the Czech police.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.20,0:19:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tenma will be transferred to\NDÃ¼sseldorf tomorrow afternoon.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.70,0:19:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You're in charge of this case.\NCome and take direct command!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.34,0:19:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Anyway good work, Lunge!\NCongratulations.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.81,0:19:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Dispatch someone\Nother than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.38,0:19:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Huh?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.58,0:19:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Prague is a nice place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.31,0:19:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.68,0:20:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides,\NI'm on vacation right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.12,0:20:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hey Lunge!\NWhat are you talking about?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.36,0:20:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hey!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.16,0:20:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.96,0:20:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I keep telling you,\Nyou can't see him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.43,0:20:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me why!\NThis country is a democracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.33,0:20:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma is already going to\Nbe deported to Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.97,0:20:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Just let me see him\Nfor a bit before you do!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.51,0:20:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like it was\Nall for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.78,0:20:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We came all this way\Nto Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.45,0:20:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Please ! Just once!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.18,0:20:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.45,0:20:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Come this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.57,0:20:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,When we interrogate people,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.44,0:20:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of person do you think\Nwe have the most trouble with?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.57,0:21:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,People who don't change their\Nexpression, no matter what we say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.31,0:21:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,People who don't talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.48,0:21:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,People like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.90,0:21:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"Love Letter from\Nthe Monster to the Beauty"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.13,0:21:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a draft for a novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.47,0:21:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"I've been watching you."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.97,0:21:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"I've been watching so\NI could devour you whole."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.38,0:21:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"But instead, everything about you\Nconsumed me."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.52,0:21:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"When I was falling apart,\Nhow did I look to you?"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.39,0:21:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"When I was falling apart,\Nthe object that you gave me..."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.16,0:21:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"You left me\Na beautiful jewel."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.70,0:21:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"The twins who look as if they\Nwere blessed with eternal life."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.00,0:22:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"The most sinful deed is to\Ntake away a person's name."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.74,0:22:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Let's get your name back."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.07,0:22:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"I'll give you your name back."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.11,0:22:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Your name is.. .Anna."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.78,0:22:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Right now,\NI'm just sad."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.72,0:22:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Sad."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.92,0:22:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Sad."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.02,0:22:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Sad."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.99,0:22:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.86,0:22:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people died\Nin that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.23,0:22:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And an incredible\Nmonster was born.
